pecially in lower-cost manufacturing locations.\n\n  * Initial outreach and consulting services\n  * Requirement analysis and design work\n  * Implementation and technology infrastructure assessment\n\n## Leveraging Existing Technology Infrastructure\n\nYee emphasizes the importance of leveraging the client\u2019s existing technology\ninfrastructure, such as Cisco or Palo Alto systems, to ensure that the\ntransition to Industry 4.0 is seamless and cost-effective. He also stresses\nthe need to consider the environmental and connectivity challenges in remote\nmanufacturing locations, highlighting the complexity and non-one-size-fits-all\nnature of the transition process.\n\n  * Understanding and leveraging existing technology infrastructure\n  * Addressing environmental and connectivity challenges in remote manufacturing locations\n\n## SASE Solutions for Secure Access and Connectivity\n\nYee discusses the critical role of Secure Access Service Edge (SASE) solutions\nin providing comprehensive security functions for manufacturing facilities. He\nhighlights the importance of zero trust networks and firewall as a service to\nensure secure access to cloud providers for remote users.\n\n  * Importance of SASE solutions for comprehensive security\n  * Zero trust networks and firewall as a service for secure access\n\nThe combination of Industry 4.0 and 5G technology is driving a significant\ntransformation in manufacturing across the Asia Pacific region. With the\nsupport of the right telecommunications carriers and service provider\npartners, manufacturers can navigate this transition and harness the full\npotential of intelligent connectivity and automation in the manufacturing\nindustry. It is crucial for manufacturing businesses to embrace these\nadvancements and leverage the expertise of telecommunications carriers and\nservice providers as business partners to ensure a seamless and secure\ntransition to Industry 4.0 and 5G technology.\n\nTags:\naianalyticsbigdataclou